[The decision whether to go forward with the Olympics is going down to the wire. Games Tokyo 2020 is scheduled to start on 23 July 2021. With approximately 1% of the Japan's population vaccinated, it seems highly risky to the athletes and those in attendance to hold the games, as disappointing as that will be. According to The Guardian, "The health ministry has so far approved only the Pfizer/BioNTech vaccine, leaving Japan dependent on imports from the EU until the AstraZeneca and Moderna vaccines are given the green light, possibly next month [May 2021]" https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/apr/26/japans-slow-covid-vaccine-rollout-casts-cloud-over-tokyo-olympics. There doesn't seem to be adequate time to achieve a level of immunity that would be safe for the games to proceed. - Mod.LK]

