[Data by country, area, or territory for 26 Apr 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Apr26_1619549024.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 25.3% of daily case numbers and 46.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 61.15 million cases. Brazil reported over 71 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by the USA with 51 809 cases, Argentina (21 220), and Columbia (16 730). 10 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Canada, Mexico, Chile, Paraguay, Guatemala, Bolivia, Uruguay, Venezuela, Puerto Rico, and Cuba). Four additional countries (Dominican Republic, Honduras, Ecuador, and Guadeloupe) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 16.9% of daily case numbers and 17.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 50.84 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium (1 case), Sweden, Norway, Switzerland, and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by France, Italy, and Germany, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 13 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 4 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.0% of daily case numbers and 7.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.87 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (19 165) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Oman, UAE, Jordan, Tunisia, Kuwait, Lebanon, and Bahrain. Morocco, Palestinian Authority, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 0.6% of daily case numbers and 0.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.28 million cases. Ethiopia (1324) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by South Africa (1101). Cameroon, Botswana, Gabon, and Congo among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.7% of daily case numbers and 3.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.35 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 17 000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, South Korea, and Mongolia.

- The South East Asia region reported 46.1% of the daily newly reported cases and 24.4% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 20.33 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 352 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (4402 cases), Nepal (3032), Bangladesh (2922), Thailand (2048), and Sri Lanka (793).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 26 Apr 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

