[In the past 24 hours, India (319 435), the USA (47 456), Turkey (37 312), and Brazil (29 669) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 10 966 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 24 Apr 2021 to late 25 Apr 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (7 countries) include India, the USA, Turkey, Brazil, Iran (21 026), Argentina (18 793), and Colombia (12 839). A total of 52 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 22 of the 52 countries are from the European region, 9 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and 3 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 5.4%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 4.1%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 16.9% decrease in daily reported cases and a 0.8% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported total is approx. 700 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours, with over 148.47 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.13 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
